original_title: US Ambassador meets Air Force Chief
original_body_lines: The Ambassador of United States of America to Sri Lanka  Julie J Chung called on the Commander of the Air Force, Air Marshal Udeni Rajapaksa on Monday (24) at Air Force Headquarters.
A cordial discussion was held between the Commander and visiting Ambassador on matters of bilateral importance after which official plaques were exchanged to mark the occasion.
The occasion was attended by Defence Attache, Lieutenant Colonel Anthony C. Nelson and Chief in the Office of Defence Cooperation, Lieutenant Commander Sean Jin.
